Parses a JSON string and extracts the object specified by the path.

The path is specified in dotted form.

Examples
----------------
```
ParseJson({ "a": { "b": "hello"}}, 'a.b') -> "hello"
ParseJson(['a', 'b', 'c'], 1) -> 'b'
ParseJson({ "03. my key": true}, '["03. my key"]') -> true
```
Full doc of the syntax supported: [jsonpath-plus](https://www.npmjs.com/package/jsonpath-plus). A list is returned when multiple results are found.
The path where the object is. Wildcard (*), recursion (..), range ([start:end:step] are supported.)
